Police say they’re investigating three cases of sexual assault. It's believed there could be even more victims, and government is appealing to others who’ve been affected to come forward. eNCA's Thuba Vilane has more. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - Former employees of Durban's China Mall say their manager raped them. Now, they want justice. On Monday, they took part in a march against gender-based violence organised by the office of the KwaZulu-Natal premier. The employees say nothing has been done since they reported their cases to the police. Memorandums were handed over to both the China Mall and the Point Road Police Station. Police say they’re investigating three cases of sexual assault. It's believed there could be even more victims, and government is appealing to others who’ve been affected to come forward. * eNCA's Thuba Vilane reports.